@startuml
title IBM Spectrum Scale Security Posture Monitoring - Runtime Flow\n(Performance & Security Focus)

actor "Cron Scheduler" as Cron
participant "cronjob.py" as CronJob
participant "fetch_security_posture_and_upload_to_ES.sh" as OrchestratorScript
participant "scale-clusters.conf" as ClusterConfig
participant "security-posture.conf" as ESConfig
participant "SSH Client" as SSH
participant "Spectrum Scale Cluster" as ScaleCluster
participant "collector/security_posture.py" as Collector
participant "split_json_for_kibana.py" as Splitter
participant "Elasticsearch" as ES
participant "Kibana Dashboard" as Kibana

== Scheduled Collection Trigger ==
Cron -> CronJob: Trigger periodic execution
activate CronJob
CronJob -> OrchestratorScript: Execute collection and upload process
activate OrchestratorScript

== Configuration Loading (Security) ==
OrchestratorScript -> ClusterConfig: Read cluster connection details\n(IP, user, temp directory)
activate ClusterConfig
ClusterConfig --> OrchestratorScript: Return cluster configuration
deactivate ClusterConfig

OrchestratorScript -> ESConfig: Read Elasticsearch credentials\n(URL, username, password)
activate ESConfig
note right: **Security Concern:**\nCredentials stored in plaintext\nShould use secrets manager
ESConfig --> OrchestratorScript: Return ES configuration
deactivate ESConfig

== Remote Data Collection (Performance & Security) ==
OrchestratorScript -> SSH: Establish SSH connection to cluster
activate SSH
SSH -> ScaleCluster: Authenticate and connect
activate ScaleCluster
note right: **Security:**\nSSH key-based authentication\nrequired for secure access
SSH --> OrchestratorScript: Connection established

OrchestratorScript -> SSH: Transfer security_posture.py to cluster
SSH -> ScaleCluster: Upload collector script via SCP
note right: **Performance:**\nMinimize data transfer overhead
ScaleCluster --> SSH: Script uploaded
SSH --> OrchestratorScript: Transfer complete

OrchestratorScript -> SSH: Execute security_posture.py
SSH -> ScaleCluster: Run collection script
ScaleCluster -> Collector: Execute security data collection
activate Collector

== Security Data Collection ==
Collector -> ScaleCluster: mmgetstate (cluster state)
ScaleCluster --> Collector: Cluster operational status

Collector -> ScaleCluster: mmlscluster (cluster config)
ScaleCluster --> Collector: Cluster configuration

Collector -> ScaleCluster: mmlsfs (filesystem properties)
note left: **Security Check:**\n- Encryption status\n- Audit logging enabled\n- ACL configuration
ScaleCluster --> Collector: Filesystem security settings

Collector -> ScaleCluster: mmlsnfs, mmlssmb (export configs)
note left: **Security Check:**\n- NFS/SMB encryption\n- Access controls
ScaleCluster --> Collector: Export security configuration

Collector -> ScaleCluster: mmlsauth (authentication methods)
note left: **Security Check:**\n- Authentication protocols\n- User validation methods
ScaleCluster --> Collector: Authentication configuration

Collector -> ScaleCluster: mmlsobject (object storage)
ScaleCluster --> Collector: Object storage security

Collector -> ScaleCluster: mmlsconfig (network security)
note left: **Security Check:**\n- Communication encryption\n- Network protocols
ScaleCluster --> Collector: Network security settings

Collector -> ScaleCluster: Check GUI, FAL, TCT status
ScaleCluster --> Collector: Service security status

Collector -> Collector: Parse and format as JSON
note right: **Performance:**\nStructured JSON format\nfor efficient processing
Collector --> ScaleCluster: security_posture.json created
deactivate Collector

ScaleCluster --> SSH: Collection complete
SSH --> OrchestratorScript: Script execution finished

== Data Transfer ==
OrchestratorScript -> SSH: Download security_posture.json via SCP
SSH -> ScaleCluster: Retrieve JSON file
note right: **Performance:**\nSingle file transfer\nto minimize network calls
ScaleCluster --> SSH: Transfer JSON data
SSH --> OrchestratorScript: JSON file downloaded
deactivate ScaleCluster
deactivate SSH

== Data Transformation (Performance Optimization) ==
OrchestratorScript -> Splitter: Split JSON for Kibana indexing
activate Splitter
note right: **Performance:**\nSplit large JSON into smaller\nfiles for efficient ES indexing
Splitter -> Splitter: Parse security_posture.json
Splitter -> Splitter: Create cluster-level JSON
Splitter -> Splitter: Create filesystems JSON array
Splitter -> Splitter: Create exports JSON array
note left: **Performance:**\nSeparate indices improve\nquery performance
Splitter --> OrchestratorScript: cluster.json, filesystems.json, exports.json
deactivate Splitter

== Elasticsearch Upload (Performance & Security) ==
OrchestratorScript -> ES: DELETE existing indices (cluster, filesystems, exports)
activate ES
note right: **Performance Issue:**\nIndex deletion can cause\ndata loss on failure\nShould use upsert instead
ES --> OrchestratorScript: Indices deleted

OrchestratorScript -> ES: POST cluster.json via curl\n(with credentials)
note right: **Security:**\nHTTPS required for\ncredential transmission
ES -> ES: Index cluster security data
ES --> OrchestratorScript: Cluster data indexed

OrchestratorScript -> ES: POST filesystems.json via curl\n(bulk upload)
note left: **Performance:**\nBulk API for efficient\nmulti-document indexing
ES -> ES: Index filesystem security data
ES --> OrchestratorScript: Filesystems data indexed

OrchestratorScript -> ES: POST exports.json via curl\n(bulk upload)
ES -> ES: Index export security data
ES --> OrchestratorScript: Exports data indexed
deactivate ES

OrchestratorScript --> CronJob: Upload complete
deactivate OrchestratorScript
CronJob --> Cron: Execution finished
deactivate CronJob

== Visualization ==
Kibana -> ES: Query security posture data
activate ES
activate Kibana
note left: **Performance:**\nIndexed data enables\nfast dashboard queries
ES --> Kibana: Return aggregated security metrics
Kibana -> Kibana: Render security dashboard
note right: **Security Visualization:**\n- Encryption coverage\n- Authentication methods\n- Audit status\n- Compliance metrics
deactivate Kibana
deactivate ES

@enduml
